   Volunteer Center, HUD
   http://www.hud.gov/volunteering/index.cfm
   Healthy communities depend on volunteers - like you! This page from the
   Housing and Urban Development (HUD) links to different national
   volunteer programs, federal volunteer programs, and national volunteer
   clearinghouses.
   Related Topics: Education  Poverty  Children  Housing, health, and the
   environment
   __________________________________________________________________


                                 Three Stars
                                # Ratings:  8
                               # Visits:  164

   National Head Start Fellowships Program
   http://www2.acf.dhhs.gov/programs/hsb/about/programs/fellows.htm
   Head Start Fellows serve as apprentices in the Head Start early
   childhood development program, learn firsthand from nationally
   recognized leaders, and help the program address significant issues
   affecting children and their families.
   Related Topics: Graduate/professional  Fellowships  Poverty  Children
   __________________________________________________________________


                                 Three Stars
                                # Ratings:  4
                               # Visits:  149

   "Put a Face on Homelessness" (HUD)
   http://www.hud.gov/december.cfm
   Put a Face on Homelessness is a public service campaign to help address
   the problem of homelessness. Enter your zip code to get a list of
   providers in your area and volunteer to help.
   Related Topics: Health care  Poverty
   __________________________________________________________________


                                 Three Stars
                                # Ratings:  4
                               # Visits:  147

   AmericaReads (US Dept of Education)
   http://www.ed.gov/inits/americareads/coluniv.html
   The America Reads Challenge is a national campaign that challenges
   every American to help all our children learn to read, including
   English Language Learners and students with disabilities. Be a
   volunteer and tutor children in reading!
   Related Topics: Education  Poverty  Children
   __________________________________________________________________


                                  One Star
                                # Ratings:  1
                                # Visits:  38

   Volunteer, Bureau of Indian Affairs (US Dept of Interior)
   http://www.doi.gov/bia/non_profit/volunteers.html
   Discover what volunteer opportunities exist with one of 554 federally
   recognized tribes. Each tribe is a sovereign domestic nation with
   varying government structures, policies, and cultures.
   Related Topics: Health care  Education  Poverty  Children  Diversity
   __________________________________________________________________


                                   Not Rated
                                # Visits:  25

   Volunteering, Neighborhood Networks (US Dept of Housing and Urban
   Development)
   http://www.hud.gov/nnw/nnwgetinvolved.html
   Neighborhood Networks establishes multi-service community technology
   centers that bring digital opportunity and lifelong learning to
   residents of insured and assisted housing. They offer some great
   volunteer opportunities.
   Related Topics: Education  Poverty  Children  Housing, health, and the
   environment

